attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the GoPro, inspects it and does not find the battery door. The instructor tells the student where the battery door is and how to open it. The student opens the battery door, pulls out the old battery and places it on the table. The student grabs the new battery, inspects the battery slot and inserts the battery in the wrong way. The student tries to close the battery door and realizes the battery is in the wrong way. The student takes out the battery, flips it, inserts it back into the battery slot and closes the battery door. The student opens the battery door and tries to pull out the Sd card. The student takes out the battery, pushes on the old Sd card and takes it out. The student places the old Sd card on the table and grabs the new one. The student inserts the new Sd card in the corresponding slot, grabs the battery, puts it back in the battery slot and closes the battery door. The student looks for the power button of the GoPro and the instructor tells the student where is located. The student presses the power button and waits for the GoPro to turn on. The student presses the power button and holds it for a couple of seconds until the GoPro turns off. The student grabs the strap and involuntarily turns on the GoPro. The student presses the power button and holds it for a couple of seconds until the GoPro turns off. The student inspects the strap but does not know how to assemble the GoPro on it. The instructor tells the student to first unscrew the lock screw from the strap and to pull out the mount of the GoPro, which the student does. The student puts the lock screw on the table, grabs the strap and assembles the mount of the GoPro on it. The student grabs the lock screw and screws the mount and strap together. The student removes the lock screw, puts it on the table and disassembles the GoPro from the strap. The student puts the strap on the table, grabs the handheld grip and puts the GoPro on the table to first remove the lock screw from the handheld grip. The student puts the lock screw on the table, grabs the GoPro and struggles to assemble it to the handheld grip. The student assembles the GoPro to the handheld grip and involuntarily turns on the GoPro. The student grabs the lock screw, screws the GoPro and handheld grip together and turns off the GoPro. The student removes the lock screw, puts it on the table and disassembles the GoPro from the handheld grip. The student places the handheld grip and the GoPro on the table, grabs the tripod and grabs again the GoPro but realizes the lock screw should be removed first. The student removes the lock screw from the tripod and places it on the table. The student grabs the GoPro and assembles it to the tripod. The student grabs the lock screw and tries to insert it on the tripod but drops it on the table. The student grabs the lock screw again and screws the GoPro and tripod together. The student removes the lock screw, places it on the table, disassembles the GoPro from the tripod, closes the mount of the GoPro and puts it on the table. The student grabs the lock screw and puts it back on the tripod. The student places the tripod on the table and grabs the handheld grip and its lock screw. The student puts the lock screw back in the handheld grip and places the handheld grip on the table. The student grabs the strap and its lock screw. The student puts the lock screw back in the strap and places the strap on the table.
